<TITLE> Industrial zones will be more active: minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Comilla, July 10 (bdnews24.com)The BSCIC industrial cities will be made more active to meet the demand for products, the industries minister said on Friday. "The current government's policy is to give assistance, as much as possible, to industrial entrepreneurs for a strong private sector," Dilip Barua said at a meeting with local industries entrepreneurs, BSCIC officials, media and civil society representatives. The minister emphasised the Public Private Partnership to solve the infrastructural problems of all the BSCIC cities, a press release issued by industries ministry quoted him as saying. He pointed out that the first budget reflected AL election manifesto. "Necessary steps have been taken by breaking past customs to protect industries in the current budget." He hoped that the budget will pave the way for a massive industrialisation. Barua also said that initiatives would be taken to modernise BSCIC industrial cities for the development of the SME sector. The industries minister earlier visited some BSCIC industrial units and saw their production. bdn
